
{{alias}}
    Regular expression to match a white space character.

    Matches the 25 characters defined as white space ("WSpace=Y","WS")
    characters in the Unicode 9.0 character database.

    Matches one related related white space character (zero width non-breaking
    space which was deprecated as of Unicode 3.2) without the Unicode character
    property "WSpace=Y".

    Examples
    --------
    > var bool = {{alias}}.test( '\n' )
    true
    > bool = {{alias}}.test( ' ' )
    true
    > bool = {{alias}}.test( 'a' )
    false
